# =============================================================================
# steelplate environment
#
# WHERE THESE GO:
#   - On Vercel: set every key below in Project → Settings → Environment
#     Variables. That is the source of truth for production & preview deploys.
#     You do NOT need a local .env for the deployed app to work.
#   - Locally: you only need a .env.local if you run `npm run dev`, the DB
#     migration, or the seed script on your machine. Easiest way to get one:
#         vercel env pull .env.local
#     Never commit .env / .env.local (already in .gitignore).
# =============================================================================

# ---- The brain: a cost-ordered chain (Gemini → Groq → Claude) ----
# Cheapest tier first; Claude is the quality backstop, not the default.
# A tier is simply skipped if its key is missing — set at least one.

# Model IDs come from src/lib/model-catalog.ts. Each MODEL var below must be an
# id from that catalog; leave unset to use the catalog default.

# Tier 0 — Gemini (default brain, also embeddings)
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=...
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash      # catalog default

# Tier 1 — Groq (first escalation: free tier, very fast)
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# Tier 2 — Claude (last-resort quality backstop only)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6     # set to claude-opus-4-8 for max quality (pricier)

# DeepSeek — cheapest reasoning. Not in the default chain, but available in the
# catalog / via modelById (e.g. for a model picker or a cheap reasoning tier).
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...

# ---- The critic & ingestion (kept cheap; never Claude) ----
CRITIC_MODEL=gemini-3.1-flash-lite   # scores each draft against the principles
INGEST_MODEL=gemini-3.1-flash-lite   # summarizing news / distilling research

# ---- Data ----
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...neon.tech/steelplate?sslmode=require
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=vercel_blob_...

# ---- Ops ----
CRON_SECRET=generate-a-long-random-string
# (The child profile is now created from the app's onboarding screen on first
#  run — no seed script or NEXT_PUBLIC_CHILD_ID needed.)

# ---- Auth (lock this down before anything real) ----
# Add Clerk or Auth.js keys here and gate every route. Handles a child's data.
